Zod doesn't have a built-in XOR combinator, but you can approximate your desired schema using unions and `.passthrough()`. For each section type, you can define a union of two object schemas: one for `{ type: S1, enabled: true, ...validation }` and one for `{ type: S1, enabled: false }` with `.passthrough()` to allow any extra fields. For example:

