In Zod v4, refinements added with `.refine()` only run after all base validations pass, so by default, you can't show refinement errors alongside base errors on an empty or invalid form. However, you can achieve your goal by switching to the `.check()` method (which replaces `.superRefine()` in v4). `.check()` lets you collect and report multiple issues in a single pass, regardless of whether base validations failed, so you can surface all errors—including cross-field or conditional ones—at once [docs](https://zod.dev/api#check).

Here's how you might refactor your schema:

```js
const formSchema = z.object({
  // ... your fields ...
}).check((data, ctx) => {
  // Example: base field checks (optional, since Zod does these already)
  // if (!data.name) ctx.addIssue({ path: ['name'], message: 'Name is required', code: z.ZodIssueCode.custom });

  // Cross-field refinements:
  if (data.age_or_dob === "dob" && !data.date_of_birth) {"},{"type":"text","text":"
    ctx.addIssue({ path: ["date_of_birth"], message: t("date_of_birth_must_be_present"), code: z.ZodIssueCode.custom });
  }
