This is expected behavior in Zod v4.1. Metadata attached via `.meta()` is stored in a registry keyed to the schema instance, and `z.toJSONSchema` merges all metadata (including custom keys) directly into the JSON Schema output as plain properties—not as `x-` vendor extensions. However, `z.fromJSONSchema` does not read or restore custom metadata fields (including `x-` extensions or any non-standard JSON Schema fields) and does not register the new schema in `z.globalRegistry` during deserialization. Only standard fields like `description` and `default` are mapped back to Zod methods; all other metadata is ignored. This means metadata and registry state are not preserved across a round-trip, by design ([source](https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/7abe4e510042cc05aafdcf4c1a80ba9c91d998f5/packages/zod/src/v4/classic/from-json-schema.ts#L16-L536)).

The rationale, as discussed by @colinhacks, is that serialization and deserialization are intentionally asymmetric: Zod's type system and metadata model do not map 1:1 to JSON Schema, and full round-trip fidelity (including metadata and registry) is considered out of scope for Zod ([source](https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/issues/4781)). There is no official workaround for preserving Zod-specific metadata or registry state across this boundary. If you need to persist metadata, you can manage it externally (e.g., alongside your schemas) and reapply it after deserialization.
"},{"type":"text","text":"
Serializing `.meta()` keys as `x-` vendor extensions and rehydrating them on deserialization is not currently supported and would require custom logic outside of Zod. There is community discussion about using custom properties (like `$zodFlags` or `$zod`) in JSON Schema output to preserve Zod-specific information, but this is not implemented in Zod ([source](https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/issues/4164)).

If this answers your question, please close the issue! If you want to propose vendor extension support as a feature, let me know and I can relay the feedback to @colinhacks.


